---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

import Content from "../components/Content.astro";
import NavPusher from "../components/NavPusher.astro";

const thayseAndNoah = "/images/thayse-noah-nyc.jpg";
---

<Layout title="More Info | Thayse & Noah" description="">
  <main class="relative bg-white">
    <img
      src={thayseAndNoah}
      alt=""
      class="fixed h-full w-full max-w-[1920px] bg-center object-cover opacity-5"
      style={{ objectPosition: "50% 50%" }}
    />
    <Content>
      <NavPusher />
      <div class="relative z-10 flex flex-col gap-8 py-20">
        <h1 class="xs:text-4xl mb-1 text-3xl font-black text-dark-2">
          More Info
        </h1>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-16">
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-black">What You Need</h2>
            <ol class="flex max-w-screen-sm flex-col gap-8">
              <li>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-black">1. Passport</h3>
                <p class="">
                  You'll need your passport to travel internationally and to
                  apply for your visa. If you don't have one, get to it ASAP! ðŸ˜ƒ
                </p>
                <div class="mt-3 flex flex-col gap-2 text-sm">
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Deadline:</h4>
                    <p class="text-thay-green-800">January 17, 2025</p>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Resources:</h4>
                    <a
                      href="https://travel.state.gov/content/travel/en/passports.html"
                      class="text-thay-green-800 underline transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:text-thay-green-900"
                      >Get or replace your passport</a
                    >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-black">2. Flight Tickets</h3>
                <p class="">
                  Below you can find our recommended departure dates for your
                  flights. If you'd like to join us, after the wedding, we'll be
                  doing some light sight-seeing in the area. All are welcome!
                  <br /><br />
                  <span class="font-bold">Vacation Trip Length</span>
                  <br />
                  <span> May 14, 2025 (Wed) - May 21, 2025 (Wed) </span>
                  <br /><br />
                  <span class="font-bold">Minimum Trip Length</span>
                  <br />
                  <span> May 15, 2025 (Thu) - May 19, 2025 (Sun) </span>
                </p>
                <div class="mt-3 flex flex-col gap-2 text-sm">
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Deadline:</h4>
                    <p class="text-thay-green-800">February 17, 2025</p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="flex flex-col">
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Resources:</h4>
                    <a
                      href="https://www.delta.com/"
                      class="text-thay-green-800 underline transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:text-thay-green-900"
                    >
                      Delta
                    </a>
                    <a
                      href="https://www.aa.com/en-us/"
                      class="text-thay-green-800 underline transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:text-thay-green-900"
                    >
                      American Airlines
                    </a>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-black">3. Hotel / Airbnb</h3>
                <p class="">
                  My beautiful fiancÃ©e compiled a list of Airbnbs and hotels in
                  safe areas. Check these out and check in with others to see if
                  it makes sense to share an Airbnb.
                </p>
                <div class="mt-3 flex flex-col gap-2 text-sm">
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Deadline:</h4>
                    <p class="text-thay-green-800">February 17, 2025</p>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Resources:</h4>
                    <a
                      href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Vl94JjOoPZrHWu5obTVI1-8YJjCsAbb2t2Kz2YF2tpw/edit?usp=sharing"
                      class="text-thay-green-800 underline transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:text-thay-green-900"
                      >Thay's Hotels and Airbnbs</a
                    >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-black">4. Travel Visa</h3>
                <p class="">
                  Brazil now requires Americans to apply for a visa to visit.
                  Fortunately this is all digital and shouldn't be too much of a
                  pain. The visa is valid for 2 years after issuance date.
                </p>
                <div class="mt-3 flex flex-col gap-2 text-sm">
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Deadline:</h4>
                    <p class="text-thay-green-800">March 17, 2025</p>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Resources:</h4>
                    <a
                      href="https://brazil.vfsevisa.com/"
                      class="text-thay-green-800 underline transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:text-thay-green-900"
                      >Apply for your e-visa here</a
                    >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-black">
              Notes and Tips About Visiting Brazil
            </h2>
            <ol class="flex max-w-screen-sm flex-col gap-8">
              <li>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-black">1. Eu nÃ£o falo inglÃªs</h3>
                <p class="">Most Brazilians do not speak english. Good luck!</p>
                <div class="mt-3 flex flex-col gap-2 text-sm">
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Tips:</h4>
                    <ul class="list-disc ps-4 text-thay-green-800">
                      <li class="">
                        <p class="">
                          Download the Google Translate app on your phone. In
                          the app, download Portuguese (Brazil), for use without
                          internet.
                        </p>
                      </li>
                      <li class="">
                        <p class="">
                          Consider learning some Portuguese basics like "Hi",
                          "Thank you", and "Do you speak english?".
                        </p>
                      </li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div class="flex flex-col">
                    <h4 class="font-bold">Resources:</h4>
                    <a
                      href="https://www.duolingo.com/"
                      class="text-thay-green-800 underline transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:text-thay-green-900"
                      >Learn Portuguese Basics with Duolingo</a
                    >
                    <a
                      href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.google.android.apps.translate&hl=en_US&pli=1"
                      class="text-thay-green-800 underline transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:text-thay-green-900"
                      >Download Google Translate - Android</a
                    >
                    <a
                      href="https://apps.apple.com/us/app/google-translate/id414706506"
                      class="text-thay-green-800 underline transition duration-300 ease-in-out hover:text-thay-green-900"
                      >Download Google Translate - iPhone</a
                    >
                  </div>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-black">2. No Need to Tip</h3>
                <p class="">
                  Brazil doesn't have the tipping culture that we do in the
                  States. Just be polite and make a good name for us Americans.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <h3 class="text-lg font-black">3. No Toilet Paper in Toilet</h3>
                <p class="">
                  There will be a small trash can next to the toilet. Put it
                  there, or go to jail.
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>
          <!-- <h2 class="text-2xl font-black">About The Trip</h2> -->
        </div>
      </div>
    </Content>
  </main>
</Layout>
